cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.MM

This paper deals with information-theoretic private information retrieval (PIR) and streaming using convolutional codes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information and communication. The paper also discusses security issues related to straggling and Byzantine servers, which suggests the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper deals with distributed storage systems, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions video streaming, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
